#. <section class="sutta" id="mn9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn9:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 9"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn9:0.2"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhisutta"
msgstr "Right View"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn9:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn9:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn9:1.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn9:1.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn9:1.6"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:2.1"
msgid "“‘Sammādiṭṭhi sammādiṭṭhī’ti, āvuso, vuccati."
msgstr "“Reverends, they speak of this thing called ‘right view’."

#. VAR: sammādiṭṭhi → sammādiṭṭhī (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "mn9:2.2"
msgid ""
"Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How do you define a noble disciple who has right view, whose view is "
"correct, who has experiential confidence in the teaching, and has come to "
"the true teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Dūratopi kho mayaṃ, āvuso, āgaccheyyāma āyasmato sāriputtassa santike "
"etassa bhāsitassa atthamaññātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, we would travel a long way to learn the meaning of this statement "
"in the presence of Venerable Sāriputta."

msgctxt "mn9:2.4"
msgid "Sādhu vatāyasmantaṃyeva sāriputtaṃ paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho."
msgstr "May Venerable Sāriputta himself please clarify the meaning of this."

msgctxt "mn9:2.5"
msgid "Āyasmato sāriputtassa sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr "The mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "mn9:2.6"
msgid "“Tena hi, āvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, reverends, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn9:2.7"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn9:2.8"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako akusalañca pajānāti, akusalamūlañca pajānāti, "
"kusalañca pajānāti, kusalamūlañca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"“A noble disciple understands the unskillful and its root, and the skillful "
"and its root."

msgctxt "mn9:3.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:4.1"
msgid ""
"Katamaṃ panāvuso, akusalaṃ, katamaṃ akusalamūlaṃ, katamaṃ kusalaṃ, katamaṃ "
"kusalamūlaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"But what is the unskillful and what is its root? And what is the skillful "
"and what is its root?"

#. VAR: pharusā vācā → pharusavācā (mr)
#. VAR: pisuṇā vācā → pisuṇavācā (mr)
msgctxt "mn9:4.2"
msgid ""
"Pāṇātipāto kho, āvuso, akusalaṃ, adinnādānaṃ akusalaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro "
"akusalaṃ, musāvādo akusalaṃ, pisuṇā vācā akusalaṃ, pharusā vācā akusalaṃ, "
"samphappalāpo akusalaṃ, abhijjhā akusalaṃ, byāpādo akusalaṃ, micchādiṭṭhi "
"akusalaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s "
"false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and covetousness, ill will, and "
"wrong view."

msgctxt "mn9:4.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso akusalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the unskillful."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:5.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, akusalamūlaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the root of the unskillful?"

msgctxt "mn9:5.2"
msgid "Lobho akusalamūlaṃ, doso akusalamūlaṃ, moho akusalamūlaṃ—"
msgstr "Greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "mn9:5.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso, akusalamūlaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the root of the unskillful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:6.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, kusalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the skillful?"

msgctxt "mn9:6.2"
msgid ""
"Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī kusalaṃ, adinnādānā veramaṇī kusalaṃ, kāmesumicchācārā "
"veramaṇī kusalaṃ, musāvādā veramaṇī kusalaṃ, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī "
"kusalaṃ, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ, samphappalāpā veramaṇī kusalaṃ, "
"anabhijjhā kusalaṃ, abyāpādo kusalaṃ, sammādiṭṭhi kusalaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Avoiding killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; avoiding "
"speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, good "
"will, and right view."

msgctxt "mn9:6.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso, kusalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the skillful."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:7.1"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, kusalamūlaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the root of the skillful?"

msgctxt "mn9:7.2"
msgid "Alobho kusalamūlaṃ, adoso kusalamūlaṃ, amoho kusalamūlaṃ—"
msgstr "Contentment, love, and understanding."

msgctxt "mn9:7.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso, kusalamūlaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the root of the skillful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ akusalaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ akusalamūlaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ kusalaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kusalamūlaṃ pajānāti, so sabbaso "
"rāgānusayaṃ pahāya, paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā, ‘asmī’ti diṭṭhimānānusayaṃ "
"samūhanitvā, avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā, diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands in this way the unskillful and its root, and "
"the skillful and its root. They’ve completely given up the underlying "
"tendency to greed, got rid of the underlying tendency to repulsion, and "
"eradicated the underlying tendency to the view and conceit ‘I am’. They’ve "
"given up ignorance and given rise to knowledge, and make an end of suffering "
"in this very life."

msgctxt "mn9:8.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: apucchuṃ → āpucchuṃ (bj) | apucchiṃsu (s1-3)
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn9:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Saying “Good, sir,” those mendicants approved and agreed with what Sāriputta "
"said. Then they asked another question:"

msgctxt "mn9:9.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā panāvuso, aññopi pariyāyo yathā ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, "
"ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ "
"saddhamman”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But reverend, could there be another way to describe a noble disciple who "
"has right view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in "
"the teaching, and has come to the true teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.48"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:10.1"
msgid "“Siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:10.2"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako āhārañca pajānāti, āhārasamudayañca pajānāti, "
"āhāranirodhañca pajānāti, āhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadañca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands fuel, its origin, its cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to its cessation."

msgctxt "mn9:10.3"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:11.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo panāvuso, āhāro, katamo āhārasamudayo, katamo āhāranirodho, katamā "
"āhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"But what is fuel? What is its origin, its cessation, and the practice that "
"leads to its cessation?"

msgctxt "mn9:11.2"
msgid ""
"Cattārome, āvuso, āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā, sambhavesīnaṃ vā "
"anuggahāya."
msgstr ""
"There are these four fuels. They maintain sentient beings that have been "
"born and help those that are about to be born."

msgctxt "mn9:11.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "mn9:11.4"
msgid ""
"Kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, "
"viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention "
"the third, and consciousness the fourth."

msgctxt "mn9:11.5"
msgid ""
"Taṇhāsamudayā āhārasamudayo, taṇhānirodhā āhāranirodho, ayameva ariyo "
"aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo āhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Fuel originates from craving. Fuel ceases when craving ceases. The practice "
"that leads to the cessation of fuel is simply this noble eightfold path, "
"that is:"

msgctxt "mn9:11.6"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto, sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo "
"sammāsati sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:12.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ āhāraṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āhārasamudayaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ āhāranirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ "
"pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya, paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā, ‘asmī’"
"ti diṭṭhimānānusayaṃ samūhanitvā, avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā, diṭṭheva "
"dhamme dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands in this way fuel, its origin, its cessation, "
"and the practice that leads to its cessation. They’ve completely given up "
"the underlying tendency to greed, got rid of the underlying tendency to "
"repulsion, and eradicated the underlying tendency to the view and conceit ‘I "
"am’. They’ve given up ignorance and given rise to knowledge, and make an end "
"of suffering in this very life."

msgctxt "mn9:12.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchuṃ:"
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir,” those mendicants … asked another question:"

msgctxt "mn9:13.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā panāvuso, aññopi pariyāyo yathā ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, "
"ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ "
"saddhamman”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But reverend, could there be another way to describe a noble disciple who … "
"has come to the true teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14-18"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.49"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:14-18.1"
msgid "“Siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.2"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako dukkhañca pajānāti, dukkhasamudayañca pajānāti, "
"dukkhanirodhañca pajānāti, dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadañca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to its cessation."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.3"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who … has come "
"to the true teaching."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.4"
msgid ""
"Katamaṃ panāvuso, dukkhaṃ, katamo dukkhasamudayo, katamo dukkhanirodho, "
"katamā dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"But what is suffering? What is its origin, its cessation, and the practice "
"that leads to its cessation?"

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.5"
msgid ""
"Jātipi dukkhā, jarāpi dukkhā, maraṇampi dukkhaṃ, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsāpi dukkhā, appiyehi sampayogopi dukkho, "
"piyehi vippayogopi dukkho, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ, saṃkhittena "
"pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā—"
msgstr ""
"Rebirth is suffering; old age is suffering; death is suffering; sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are suffering; association with the "
"disliked is suffering; separation from the liked is suffering; not getting "
"what you wish for is suffering. In brief, the five grasping aggregates are "
"suffering."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.6"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso, dukkhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called suffering."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.7"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, dukkhasamudayo?"
msgstr "And what is the origin of suffering?"

#. VAR: ponobbhavikā → ponobhavikā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn9:14-18.8"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and "
"greed, looking for enjoyment in various different realms. That is,"

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.9"
msgid "kāmataṇhā bhavataṇhā vibhavataṇhā—"
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving for continued existence, and craving "
"to end existence."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.10"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, dukkhasamudayo."
msgstr "This is called the origin of suffering."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.11"
msgid "Katamo cāvuso, dukkhanirodho?"
msgstr "And what is the cessation of suffering?"

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.12"
msgid ""
"Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing "
"left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not clinging to "
"it."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.13"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, dukkhanirodho."
msgstr "This is called the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.14"
msgid "Katamā cāvuso, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering?"

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.15"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.16"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi—"
msgstr "right view … right immersion."

msgctxt "mn9:14-18.17"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā."
msgstr "This is called the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:19.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ dukkhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhasamudayaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ "
"pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya, paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā, ‘asmī’"
"ti diṭṭhimānānusayaṃ samūhanitvā, avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā, diṭṭheva "
"dhamme dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands in this way suffering, its origin, its "
"cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation. They’ve completely "
"given up the underlying tendency to greed, got rid of the underlying "
"tendency to repulsion, and eradicated the underlying tendency to the view "
"and conceit ‘I am’. They’ve given up ignorance and given rise to knowledge, "
"and make an end of suffering in this very life."

msgctxt "mn9:19.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchuṃ:"
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir,” those mendicants … asked another question:"

msgctxt "mn9:20.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā panāvuso, aññopi pariyāyo yathā ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, "
"ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ "
"saddhamman”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But reverend, could there be another way to describe a noble disciple who … "
"has come to the true teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21-22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:21-22.1"
msgid "“Siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.2"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako jarāmaraṇañca pajānāti, jarāmaraṇasamudayañca "
"pajānāti, jarāmaraṇanirodhañca pajānāti, jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ "
"paṭipadañca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands old age and death, their origin, their "
"cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation …"

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.3"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.4"
msgid ""
"Katamaṃ panāvuso, jarāmaraṇaṃ, katamo jarāmaraṇasamudayo, katamo "
"jarāmaraṇanirodho, katamā jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"But what are old age and death? What is their origin, their cessation, and "
"the practice that leads to their cessation?"

#. VAR: Yā → yaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn9:21-22.5"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhi tamhi sattanikāye jarā jīraṇatā khaṇḍiccaṃ "
"pāliccaṃ valittacatā āyuno saṃhāni indriyānaṃ paripāko—"
msgstr ""
"The old age, decrepitude, broken teeth, gray hair, wrinkly skin, diminished "
"vitality, and failing faculties of the various sentient beings in the "
"various orders of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, jarā."
msgstr "This is called old age."

# Text lacks a corresponding “what is old age” on the previous section.
msgctxt "mn9:21-22.7"
msgid "Katamañcāvuso, maraṇaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is death?"

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.8"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā tamhā sattanikāyā cuti cavanatā bhedo "
"antaradhānaṃ maccu maraṇaṃ kālaṃkiriyā khandhānaṃ bhedo, kaḷevarassa "
"nikkhepo, jīvitindriyassupacchedo—"
msgstr ""
"The passing away, perishing, disintegration, demise, mortality, death, "
"decease, breaking up of the aggregates, laying to rest of the corpse, and "
"cutting off of the life faculty of the various sentient beings in the "
"various orders of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.9"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso, maraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is called death."

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.10"
msgid "Iti ayañca jarā idañca maraṇaṃ—"
msgstr "Such is old age, and such is death."

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.11"
msgid "idaṃ vuccatāvuso, jarāmaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is called old age and death."

# Here, translating jati as “birth” obviously doesn’t work. You don’t stop getting old when your birth is over. What it means is the process of rebirth in samsara.
msgctxt "mn9:21-22.12"
msgid ""
"Jātisamudayā jarāmaraṇasamudayo, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho, ayameva "
"ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Old age and death originate from rebirth. Old age and death cease when "
"rebirth ceases. The practice that leads to the cessation of old age and "
"death is simply this noble eightfold path …”"

msgctxt "mn9:21-22.13"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:23.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ jarāmaraṇaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ "
"jarāmaraṇasamudayaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ jarāmaraṇanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ "
"jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya … "
"pe … dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:23.2"
msgid ""
