#. <a class="nya" id="nya56-58"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:56-58.1"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti kho … pe … apucchuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.2"
msgid "siyā panāvuso … pe …"
msgstr "“Could there be another way …?”"

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.3"
msgid "“siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.4"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako viññāṇañca pajānāti, viññāṇasamudayañca "
"pajānāti, viññāṇanirodhañca pajānāti, viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadañca "
"pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands consciousness, its origin, its cessation, and "
"the practice that leads to its cessation …"

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.5"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.6"
msgid ""
"Katamaṃ panāvuso, viññāṇaṃ, katamo viññāṇasamudayo, katamo viññāṇanirodho, "
"katamā viññāṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"But what is consciousness? What is its origin, its cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to its cessation?"

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.7"
msgid "Chayime, āvuso, viññāṇakāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of consciousness."

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.8"
msgid ""
"cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, sotaviññāṇaṃ, ghānaviññāṇaṃ, jivhāviññāṇaṃ, kāyaviññāṇaṃ, "
"manoviññāṇaṃ."
msgstr "Eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind consciousness."

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.9"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhārasamudayā viññāṇasamudayo, saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho, ayameva "
"ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo viññāṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Consciousness originates from choices. Consciousness ceases when choices "
"cease. The practice that leads to the cessation of consciousness is simply "
"this noble eightfold path …”"

msgctxt "mn9:56-58.10"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya59"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.54"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:59.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ viññāṇaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ viññāṇasamudayaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ "
"paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya … pe … dukkhassantakaro "
"hoti—"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya60-62"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:60-62.1"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.2"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti kho … pe … apucchuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.3"
msgid "siyā panāvuso … pe …"
msgstr "“Could there be another way …?”"

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.4"
msgid "“siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.5"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako saṅkhāre ca pajānāti, saṅkhārasamudayañca "
"pajānāti, saṅkhāranirodhañca pajānāti, saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadañca "
"pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands choices, their origin, their cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to their cessation …"

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.6"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.7"
msgid ""
"Katame panāvuso, saṅkhārā, katamo saṅkhārasamudayo, katamo saṅkhāranirodho, "
"katamā saṅkhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"But what are choices? What is their origin, their cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to their cessation?"

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.8"
msgid "Tayome, āvuso, saṅkhārā—"
msgstr "There are these three kinds of choice."

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.9"
msgid "kāyasaṅkhāro, vacīsaṅkhāro, cittasaṅkhāro."
msgstr "Choices by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.10"
msgid ""
"Avijjāsamudayā saṅkhārasamudayo, avijjānirodhā saṅkhāranirodho, ayameva "
"ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Choices originate from ignorance. Choices cease when ignorance ceases. The "
"practice that leads to the cessation of choices is simply this noble "
"eightfold path …”"

msgctxt "mn9:60-62.11"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya63"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:63.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ saṅkhāre pajānāti, evaṃ saṅkhārasamudayaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ "
"paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya, paṭighānusayaṃ "
"paṭivinodetvā, ‘asmī’ti diṭṭhimānānusayaṃ samūhanitvā, avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ "
"uppādetvā, diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:63.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya64-66"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:64-66.1"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti kho … pe … apucchuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.2"
msgid "siyā panāvuso … pe …"
msgstr "“Could there be another way …?”"

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.3"
msgid "“siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.4"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako avijjañca pajānāti, avijjāsamudayañca pajānāti, "
"avijjānirodhañca pajānāti, avijjānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadañca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands ignorance, its origin, its cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to its cessation …"

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.5"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.6"
msgid ""
"Katamā panāvuso, avijjā, katamo avijjāsamudayo, katamo avijjānirodho, katamā "
"avijjānirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"But what is ignorance? What is its origin, its cessation, and the practice "
"that leads to its cessation?"

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.7"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso, dukkhe aññāṇaṃ, dukkhasamudaye aññāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhe "
"aññāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya aññāṇaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Not knowing about suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.8"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, avijjā."
msgstr "This is called ignorance."

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.9"
msgid ""
"Āsavasamudayā avijjāsamudayo, āsavanirodhā avijjānirodho, ayameva ariyo "
"aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo avijjānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Ignorance originates from defilement. Ignorance ceases when defilement "
"ceases. The practice that leads to the cessation of ignorance is simply this "
"noble eightfold path …”"

msgctxt "mn9:64-66.10"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya67"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:67.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ avijjaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ avijjāsamudayaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ avijjānirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ avijjānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ "
"pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya, paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā, ‘asmī’"
"ti diṭṭhimānānusayaṃ samūhanitvā, avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā, diṭṭheva "
"dhamme dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn9:67.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya68"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.55"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:68.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Saying “Good, sir,” those mendicants approved and agreed with what Sāriputta "
"said. Then they asked another question:"

msgctxt "mn9:68.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā panāvuso, aññopi pariyāyo yathā ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, "
"ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ "
"saddhamman”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But reverend, could there be another way to describe a noble disciple who "
"has right view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in "
"the teaching, and has come to the true teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya69"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:69.1"
msgid "“Siyā, āvuso."
msgstr "“There could, reverends."

msgctxt "mn9:69.2"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako āsavañca pajānāti, āsavasamudayañca pajānāti, "
"āsavanirodhañca pajānāti, āsavanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadañca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands defilement, its origin, its cessation, and the "
"practice that leads to its cessation."

msgctxt "mn9:69.3"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya70"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:70.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo panāvuso, āsavo, katamo āsavasamudayo, katamo āsavanirodho, katamā "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti?"
msgstr ""
"But what is defilement? What is its origin, its cessation, and the practice "
"that leads to its cessation?"

msgctxt "mn9:70.2"
msgid "Tayome, āvuso, āsavā—"
msgstr "There are these three defilements."

msgctxt "mn9:70.3"
msgid "kāmāsavo, bhavāsavo, avijjāsavo."
msgstr "The defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "mn9:70.4"
msgid ""
"Avijjāsamudayā āsavasamudayo, avijjānirodhā āsavanirodho, ayameva ariyo "
"aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Defilement originates from ignorance. Defilement ceases when ignorance "
"ceases. The practice that leads to the cessation of defilement is simply "
"this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn9:70.5"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya71"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:71.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako evaṃ āsavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āsavasamudayaṃ "
"pajānāti, evaṃ āsavanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āsavanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ "
"pajānāti, so sabbaso rāgānusayaṃ pahāya, paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā, ‘asmī’"
"ti diṭṭhimānānusayaṃ samūhanitvā, avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā, diṭṭheva "
"dhamme dukkhassantakaro hoti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple understands in this way defilement, its origin, its "
"cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation. They’ve completely "
"given up the underlying tendency to greed, got rid of the underlying "
"tendency to repulsion, and eradicated the underlying tendency to the view "
"and conceit ‘I am’. They’ve given up ignorance and given rise to knowledge, "
"and make an end of suffering in this very life."

msgctxt "mn9:71.2"
msgid ""
"ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ujugatāssa diṭṭhi, "
"dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, āgato imaṃ saddhamman”ti."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve done this, they’re defined as a noble disciple who has right "
"view, whose view is correct, who has experiential confidence in the "
"teaching, and has come to the true teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "mn9:71.3"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā sāriputto."
msgstr "This is what Venerable Sāriputta said."

msgctxt "mn9:71.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what Sāriputta said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
